This paper is about developing a dialogue generation agent, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques such as data augmentation and ensemble methods, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The use of encoder-decoder structures and neural networks also suggests a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves knowledge-driven dialogue generation, which could potentially fall under the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
